29 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
30 Section 1. Section 13A-11-8, Code of Alabama 1975, is
31 amended to read as follows:
32 "§13A-11-8
33 (a)(1) HARASSMENT. A person commits the crime of
34 harassment if, with intent to harass, annoy, or alarm another
35 personindividual, he or she eitherdoes either of the
36 following:
37 a. Strikes, shoves, kicks, or otherwise touches a
38 person any individual or subjects him or her any individual to
39 physical contact.
40 b. Directs abusive or obscene language or makes an
41 obscene gesture towards toward another personindividual.
42 (2) For purposes of this section, harassment shall
43 include a threat, verbal or nonverbal, made with the intent to
44 carry out the threat, that would cause a reasonable person
45 individual who is the target of the threat to fear for his or
46 her safety.
47 (3) Harassment is a Class C misdemeanor.
48 (b)(1) HARASSING COMMUNICATIONS. A person commits the
49 crime of harassing communications if, with intent to harass or
50 alarm another personindividual, he or she does any of the
51 following:
52 a. Communicates with a personany individual,
53 anonymously or otherwise, by telephone, telegraph, mail, or
54 any other form of written or electronic communication, in a
55 manner likely to harass or cause alarm.
56 b. Makes a telephone call, whether or not a
